src/lib/components/ExtraDashUiComponents.description:
ExampleComponent is an example component.
It takes a property, `label`, and
displays it.
It renders an input with the property `value`
which is editable by the user.

id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks.

label.description: A label that will be printed when this component is rendered.

value.description: The value displayed in the input.

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called to report property changes
to Dash, to make them available for callbacks.

src/lib/components/OrganizationChart/Org.description:
OrganizationChartComponent is a component to nicely display a data tree.
It takes a property, `value`, which is the actual data object
creates a hierachy tree which is then rendered.
Other inputs are `selectionMode`, `selection`, `className` and `style`
which are optional. Defaults will be applied unless provided by the user.

id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks.

selectionMode.description: Defines the selection mode, valid values "single" or "multiple".

selection.description: A single treenode instance or an array to refer to the selections.

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called to report property changes
to Dash, to make them available for callbacks.
